|-
| colspan=5 | <hr>
|- valign=top
| '''EMS'''<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.motorauthority.com/blog/1030815_dutch-university-working-on-affordable-electromagnetic-suspension |title = Dutch university working on affordable electromagnetic suspension |first = Nelson |last = Ireson |publisher = MotorAuthority.com |date = 2008-11-14 |access-date = 2010-12-03 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090929043111/http://www.motorauthority.com/blog/1030815_dutch-university-working-on-affordable-electromagnetic-suspension |archive-date = 2009-09-29 |dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://techon.nikkeibp.co.jp/english/NEWS_EN/20061030/122929/ |first = Keisuke |last = Ogawa |title = Hitachi Exhibits Electromagnetic Suspension System |publisher = techon.nikkeibp.co.jp |date = 2006-10-30 |accessdate = 2010-12-03 |archive-date = 2011-10-25 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111025163445/http://techon.nikkeibp.co.jp/english/NEWS_EN/20061030/122929/ |dead-url = no }}</ref> <br />（'''{{link-en|電磁力懸浮|Electromagnetic suspension}}'''<br />或'''常導型懸浮'''）
| 列車內外的磁場較電動力懸浮低。技術上時速可達500公里。沒有車輪或二級推進系統需要。造價成本低廉。
| 列車與軌道之間分離，兩者之間的電磁吸引力容易不穩定，必須不斷透過電腦系統進行監測和糾正以免發生碰撞。由於系統固有的不穩定性和外部系統需要不斷修正，振動可能會導致系統出現問題。
|-
| colspan=5 | <hr>
|- valign=top
| '''EDS'''<ref>{{cite journal |url = http://www.thompsonrd.com/ieee_maglev_part2.pdf |format = PDF |title = Flux-Canceling Electrodynamic Maglev Suspension: Part II Test Results and Scaling Laws |author = Marc T. Thompson |coauthor = Richard D. Thornton |journal = IEEE Transactions on Magnetics |volume = 35 |issue = 3 |date = May 1999 |access-date = 2010-12-03 |archive-date = 2011-07-17 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110717051625/http://www.thompsonrd.com/ieee_maglev_part2.pdf |dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/04/nyregion/it-floats-it-speeds-it-s-a-train.html |first = Valarie |last = Cotsalas |title = It Floats! It Speeds! It's a Train! |publisher = New York Times |date = 2000-06-04 |accessdate = 2010-12-03 |archive-date = 2012-04-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120410142543/http://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/04/nyregion/it-floats-it-speeds-it-s-a-train.html |dead-url = no }}</ref> <br />（'''{{link-en|電動力懸浮|Electrodynamic_suspension}}'''<br />或'''超導型懸浮'''）
|| 內建磁鐵大幅度使用於列車與軌道，技術上時速可達603公里，比電磁力懸浮還要更快，且具備高負載的能力。已於2005年12月證明使用廉價的[[液氮|液態氮]]冷卻高溫超導磁體，能成功在船上操作。
|| 強大的磁場令列車上的乘客無法使用心律調節器或磁性數據儲存裝置（如硬碟及信用卡），因此需要使用{{le|磁屏蔽|magnetic shielding}}。軌道的誘導性會限制列車的最高速度，列車必須有[[輪|輪]]作低速運行。造價成本昂貴。
|-
| colspan=5 | <hr>
|- valign=top
| '''永磁性EDS'''<ref name=anew>{{cite web |url = http://www.llnl.gov/str/Post.html |title = ''A New Approach for Magnetically Levitating Trains—and Rockets'' |publisher = llnl.gov |accessdate = 2009-09-07 |archive-date = 2010-05-28 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100528141314/https://www.llnl.gov/str//Post.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skytran.net/press/sciam01.htm |author=Richard F. Post |title=MagLev: A New Approach |publisher=''Scientific American'' |date=January 2000 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050309114627/http://www.skytran.net/press/sciam01.htm |archivedate=2005-03-09 }}</ref> <br />（'''{{link-en|Inductrack|Inductrack}}'''）
|| 有[[失效安全|故障安全防護]][[懸吊系統|懸吊系統]]，磁鐵不需電力供給；磁場固定在列車的下面；能在低速時（大約5 km/h）產生足夠的磁場使磁浮列車懸浮；停電時列車會逐漸減速以保障安全；{{link-en|Halbach array|Halbach array}}永久磁鐵比電磁鐵可能更符合成本效益。
|| 在列車停止時，仍需要輪或軌道的一段繼續運動。
|}

== 現存系統 ==
磁浮技术分为轨道、车辆、牵引、运行控制四大系统，有16项核心技术。韩国、德國、日本與中國為世界上目前有磁浮列車試驗或營運路線的國家。

